5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to federal tax credits; to provide for the
10 State of Alabama's participation in the federal tax credit for
11 individuals who make qualified contributions to scholarship
12 granting organizations.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
14 Section 1. (a) The Legislature voluntarily elects the
15 State of Alabama to participate in the federal tax credit
16 established under 26 U.S.C. § 25F for individuals who make
17 qualified contributions to scholarship granting organizations.
18
19 (b) The Department of Revenue shall annually submit to
20 the U.S. Secretary of the Treasury and publish on the
21 Department of Revenue's website a list of all scholarship
22 granting organizations that meet the requirements under 26
23 U.S.C. § 25F and are located in this state. The Department of
24 Revenue shall certify to the U.S. Secretary of the Treasury
25 the Department of Revenue's authority to submit the list on
26 behalf of the state and comply with the requirements of 26
27 U.S.C. § 25F, including any applicable federal regulations or
28 guidance, to ensure that the state is eligible to participate
Page 1

guidance, to ensure that the state is eligible to participate
HB342 Engrossed
29 in taxable years beginning after December 31, 2026.
30 (c) The Department of Revenue may establish rules for
31 the implementation and administration of this act.
32 Section 2. This act shall become effective immediately.
